{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_d27d4860716b4cbf91145690","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t|  |downloads| |stars| |forks| |contributors|\n2\t|  |version| |packages| |license|\n3\t|  |github-actions| |doc| |twitter|\n4\t\n5\t.. |downloads| image:: https://img.shields.io/pypi/dm/pyftpdlib.svg\n6\t    :target: https://pepy.tech/project/pyftpdlib\n7\t    :alt: Downloads\n8\t\n9\t.. |stars| image:: https://img.shields.io/github/stars/giampaolo/pyftpdlib.svg\n10\t    :target: https://github.com/giampaolo/pyftpdlib/stargazers\n11\t    :alt: Github stars\n12\t\n13\t.. |forks| image:: https://img.shields.io/github/forks/giampaolo/pyftpdlib.svg\n14\t    :target: https://github.com/giampaolo/pyftpdlib/network/members\n15\t    :alt: Github forks\n16\t\n17\t.. |contributors| image:: https://img.shields.io/github/contributors/giampaolo/pyftpdlib.svg\n18\t    :target: https://github.com/giampaolo/pyftpdlib/graphs/contributors\n19\t    :alt: Contributors\n20\t\n21\t.. |github-actions| image:: https://img.shields.io/github/actions/workflow/status/giampaolo/pyftpdlib/.github/workflows/tests.yml\n22\t    :target: https://github.com/giampaolo/pyftpdlib/actions\n23\t    :alt: GH actions\n24\t\n25\t.. |doc| image:: https://readthedocs.org/projects/pyftpdlib/badge/?version=latest\n26\t    :target: https://pyftpdlib.readthedocs.io/en/latest/\n27\t    :alt: Documentation Status\n28\t\n29\t.. |version| image:: https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/pyftpdlib.svg?label=pypi\n30\t    :target: https://pypi.org/project/pyftpdlib\n31\t    :alt: Latest version\n32\t\n33\t.. |py-versions| image:: https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/psutil.svg\n34\t    :alt: Supported Python versions\n35\t\n36\t.. |packages| image:: https://repology.org/badge/tiny-repos/python:pyftpdlib.svg\n37\t    :target: https://repology.org/metapackage/python:pyftpdlib/versions\n38\t    :alt: Binary packages\n39\t\n40\t.. |license| image:: https://img.shields.io/github/license/giampaolo/pyftpdlib\n41\t    :target: https://github.com/giampaolo/pyftpdlib/blob/master/LICENSE\n42\t    :alt: License\n43\t\n44\t.. |twitter| image:: https://img.shields.io/twitter/follow/grodola?style=flat\n45\t    :target: https://twitter.com/grodola\n46\t    :alt: Twitter Follow\n47\t\n48\tQuick links\n49\t===========\n50\t\n51\t- `Home`_\n52\t- `Documentation`_\n53\t- `Download`_\n54\t- `Mailing list`_\n55\t- `What's new`_\n56\t\n57\tAbout\n58\t=====\n59\t\n60\tPython FTP server library provides a high-level portable interface to easily\n61\twrite very efficient, scalable and asynchronous FTP servers with Python. It is\n62\tthe most complete `RFC-959`_ FTP server implementation available for the\n63\t`Python`_ programming language.\n64\t\n65\tFeatures\n66\t========\n67\t\n68\t- Extremely **lightweight**, **fast** and **scalable** (see\n69\t  `why <https://github.com/giampaolo/pyftpdlib/issues/203>`__ and\n70\t  `benchmarks`_).\n71\t- Uses **sendfile(2)** (see `pysendfile <https://github.com/giampaolo/pysendfile>`__)\n72\t  system call for uploads (Linux only).\n73\t- Uses ``epoll()`` / ``kqueue()`` / ``select()`` to handle concurrency\n74\t  asynchronously.\n75\t- ...But can optionally skip to a `multiple thread / process`_ model (as in:\n76\t  you'll be free to block or use slow filesystems).\n77\t- Portable: entirely written in pure Python.\n78\t- Supports **FTPS** (`RFC-4217`_), **IPv6** (`RFC-2428`_), **Unicode** file\n79\t  names (`RFC-2640`_), **MLSD/MLST** commands (`RFC-3659`_).\n80\t- Support for virtual users and virtual filesystem.\n81\t- Flexible system of \"authorizers\" able to manage both \"virtual\" and\n82\t  \"real\" users on on both\n83\t  `UNIX <https://pyftpdlib.readthedocs.io/en/latest/tutorial.html#unix-ftp-server>`__\n84\t  and\n85\t  `Windows <https://pyftpdlib.readthedocs.io/en/latest/tutorial.html#windows-ftp-server>`__.\n86\t\n87\tPerformance\n88\t===========\n89\t\n90\tDespite being written in an interpreted language, pyftpdlib has transfer rates\n91\tcomparable or superior to common UNIX FTP servers written in C. It usually\n92\ttends to scale better (see `benchmarks`_) because whereas vsftpd and proftpd\n93\tuse multiple processes to achieve concurrency, pyftpdlib only uses one (see\n94\t`the C10K problem`_).\n95\t\n96\tpyftpdlib vs. proftpd 1.3.4\n97\t---------------------------\n98\t\n99\t+-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n100\t| **benchmark type**                      | **pyftpdlib**  | **proftpd**    | **speedup** |\n101\t+-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n102\t| STOR (client -> server)                 |  585.90 MB/sec | 600.49 MB/sec  | -0.02x      |\n103\t+-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n104\t| RETR (server -> client)                 | 1652.72 MB/sec | 1524.05 MB/sec | **+0.08**   |\n105\t+-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n106\t| 300 concurrent clients (connect, login) |    0.19 secs   | 9.98 secs      | **+51x**    |\n107\t+-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n108\t| STOR (1 file with 300 idle clients)     |  585.59 MB/sec | 518.55 MB/sec  | **+0.1x**   |\n109\t+-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n110\t| RETR (1 file with 300 idle clients)     | 1497.58 MB/sec | 1478.19 MB/sec | 0x          |\n111\t+-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n112\t| 300 concurrent clients (RETR 10M file)  |    3.41 secs   | 3.60 secs      | **+0.05x**  |\n113\t+-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n114\t| 300 concurrent clients (STOR 10M file)  |    8.60 secs   | 11.56 secs     | **+0.3x**   |\n115\t+-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n116\t| 300 concurrent clients (QUIT)           |    0.03 secs   | 0.39 secs      | **+12x**    |\n117\t+-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n118\t\n119\tpyftpdlib vs. vsftpd 2.3.5\n120\t--------------------------\n121\t\n122\t+-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n123\t| **benchmark type**                      | **pyftpdlib**  | **vsftpd**     | **speedup** |\n124\t+-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n125\t| STOR (client -> server)                 |  585.90 MB/sec | 611.73 MB/sec  | -0.04x      |\n126\t+-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n127\t| RETR (server -> client)                 | 1652.72 MB/sec | 1512.92 MB/sec | **+0.09**   |\n128\t+-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n129\t| 300 concurrent clients (connect, login) |    0.19 secs   | 20.39 secs     | **+106x**   |\n130\t+-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n131\t| STOR (1 file with 300 idle clients)     |  585.59 MB/sec | 610.23 MB/sec  | -0.04x      |\n132\t+-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n133\t| RETR (1 file with 300 idle clients)     | 1497.58 MB/sec | 1493.01 MB/sec | 0x          |\n134\t+-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n135\t| 300 concurrent clients (RETR 10M file)  |    3.41 secs   | 3.67 secs      | **+0.07x**  |\n136\t+-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n137\t| 300 concurrent clients (STOR 10M file)  |    8.60 secs   | 9.82 secs      | **+0.07x**  |\n138\t+-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n139\t| 300 concurrent clients (QUIT)           |    0.03 secs   | 0.01 secs      | +0.14x      |\n140\t+-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n141\t\n142\tFor more benchmarks see `here <https://pyftpdlib.readthedocs.io/en/latest/benchmarks.html>`__.\n143\t\n144\tCommand line usage\n145\t==================\n146\t\n147\tStart an anonymous FTP server on port 2121:\n148\t\n149\t.. code-block:: sh\n150\t\n151\t    $ python3 -m pyftpdlib\n152\t    [I 2024-06-23 13:49:35] >>> starting FTP server on 0.0.0.0:2121, pid=763634 <<<\n153\t\n154\tSame but with write permissions (useful to setup a quick and dirty file sharing server):\n155\t\n156\t.. code-block:: sh\n157\t\n158\t    $ python3 -m pyftpdlib --write\n159\t    [I 2024-06-23 13:49:35] >>> starting FTP server on 0.0.0.0:2121, pid=763641 <<<\n160\t\n161\tAlso see `CLI doc <https://pyftpdlib.readthedocs.io/en/latest/cli.html>`__\n162\tfor more command line examples.\n163\t\n164\tAPI usage\n165\t=========\n166\t\n167\t.. code-block:: python\n168\t\n169\t    >>> from pyftpdlib.authorizers import DummyAuthorizer\n170\t    >>> from pyftpdlib.handlers import FTPHandler\n171\t    >>> from pyftpdlib.servers import FTPServer\n172\t    >>>\n173\t    >>> authorizer = DummyAuthorizer()\n174\t    >>> authorizer.add_user(\"user\", \"12345\", \"/home/giampaolo\", perm=\"elradfmwMT\")\n175\t    >>> authorizer.add_anonymous(\"/home/nobody\")\n176\t    >>>\n177\t    >>> handler = FTPHandler\n178\t    >>> handler.authorizer = authorizer\n179\t    >>>\n180\t    >>> server = FTPServer((\"127.0.0.1\", 21), handler)\n181\t    >>> server.serve_forever()\n182\t    [I 13-02-19 10:55:42] >>> starting FTP server on 127.0.0.1:21 <<<\n183\t    [I 13-02-19 10:55:42] poller: <class 'pyftpdlib.ioloop.Epoll'>\n184\t    [I 13-02-19 10:55:42] masquerade (NAT) address: None\n185\t    [I 13-02-19 10:55:42] passive ports: None\n186\t    [I 13-02-19 10:55:42] use sendfile(2): True\n187\t    [I 13-02-19 10:55:45] 127.0.0.1:34178-[] FTP session opened (connect)\n188\t    [I 13-02-19 10:55:48] 127.0.0.1:34178-[user] USER 'user' logged in.\n189\t    [I 13-02-19 10:56:27] 127.0.0.1:34179-[user] RETR /home/giampaolo/.vimrc completed=1 bytes=1700 seconds=0.001\n190\t    [I 13-02-19 10:56:39] 127.0.0.1:34179-[user] FTP session closed (disconnect).\n191\t\n192\tFor other code samples read the `tutorial <https://pyftpdlib.readthedocs.io/en/latest/tutorial.html>`__\n193\t\n194\tDonate\n195\t======\n196\t\n197\tA lot of time and effort went into making pyftpdlib as it is right now.\n198\tIf you feel pyftpdlib is useful to you or your business and want to support its\n199\tfuture development please consider `donating`_ me some money.\n200\t\n201\t.. _`benchmarks`: https://pyftpdlib.readthedocs.io/en/latest/benchmarks.html\n202\t.. _`Documentation`: https://pyftpdlib.readthedocs.io\n203\t.. _`donating`: https://gmpy.dev/donate\n204\t.. _`Download`: https://pypi.org/project/pyftpdlib/\n205\t.. _`Home`: https://github.com/giampaolo/pyftpdlib\n206\t.. _`Mailing list`: https://groups.google.com/group/pyftpdlib/topics\n207\t.. _`multiple thread / process`: https://pyftpdlib.readthedocs.io/en/latest/tutorial.html#changing-the-concurrency-model\n208\t.. _`Python`: https://www.python.org/\n209\t.. _`RFC-2428`: https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc2428\n210\t.. _`RFC-2640`: https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc2640\n211\t.. _`RFC-3659`: https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc3659\n212\t.. _`RFC-4217`: https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc4217\n213\t.. _`RFC-959`: https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc959.html\n214\t.. _`the C10K problem`: http://www.kegel.com/c10k.html\n215\t.. _`What's new`: https://github.com/giampaolo/pyftpdlib/blob/master/HISTORY.rst\n216\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f79157cc-9e88-4e11-b284-6901db0a6656","uuid":"29789a1e-8cfb-41f8-9732-07d127704af2","timestamp":"2026-04-07T00:09:37.822Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/README.rst","content":"|  |downloads| |stars| |forks| |contributors|\n|  |version| |packages| |license|\n|  |github-actions| |doc| |twitter|\n\n.. |downloads| image:: https://img.shields.io/pypi/dm/pyftpdlib.svg\n    :target: https://pepy.tech/project/pyftpdlib\n    :alt: Downloads\n\n.. |stars| image:: https://img.shields.io/github/stars/giampaolo/pyftpdlib.svg\n    :target: https://github.com/giampaolo/pyftpdlib/stargazers\n    :alt: Github stars\n\n.. |forks| image:: https://img.shields.io/github/forks/giampaolo/pyftpdlib.svg\n    :target: https://github.com/giampaolo/pyftpdlib/network/members\n    :alt: Github forks\n\n.. |contributors| image:: https://img.shields.io/github/contributors/giampaolo/pyftpdlib.svg\n    :target: https://github.com/giampaolo/pyftpdlib/graphs/contributors\n    :alt: Contributors\n\n.. |github-actions| image:: https://img.shields.io/github/actions/workflow/status/giampaolo/pyftpdlib/.github/workflows/tests.yml\n    :target: https://github.com/giampaolo/pyftpdlib/actions\n    :alt: GH actions\n\n.. |doc| image:: https://readthedocs.org/projects/pyftpdlib/badge/?version=latest\n    :target: https://pyftpdlib.readthedocs.io/en/latest/\n    :alt: Documentation Status\n\n.. |version| image:: https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/pyftpdlib.svg?label=pypi\n    :target: https://pypi.org/project/pyftpdlib\n    :alt: Latest version\n\n.. |py-versions| image:: https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/psutil.svg\n    :alt: Supported Python versions\n\n.. |packages| image:: https://repology.org/badge/tiny-repos/python:pyftpdlib.svg\n    :target: https://repology.org/metapackage/python:pyftpdlib/versions\n    :alt: Binary packages\n\n.. |license| image:: https://img.shields.io/github/license/giampaolo/pyftpdlib\n    :target: https://github.com/giampaolo/pyftpdlib/blob/master/LICENSE\n    :alt: License\n\n.. |twitter| image:: https://img.shields.io/twitter/follow/grodola?style=flat\n    :target: https://twitter.com/grodola\n    :alt: Twitter Follow\n\nQuick links\n===========\n\n- `Home`_\n- `Documentation`_\n- `Download`_\n- `Mailing list`_\n- `What's new`_\n\nAbout\n=====\n\nPython FTP server library provides a high-level portable interface to easily\nwrite very efficient, scalable and asynchronous FTP servers with Python. It is\nthe most complete `RFC-959`_ FTP server implementation available for the\n`Python`_ programming language.\n\nFeatures\n========\n\n- Extremely **lightweight**, **fast** and **scalable** (see\n  `why <https://github.com/giampaolo/pyftpdlib/issues/203>`__ and\n  `benchmarks`_).\n- Uses **sendfile(2)** (see `pysendfile <https://github.com/giampaolo/pysendfile>`__)\n  system call for uploads (Linux only).\n- Uses ``epoll()`` / ``kqueue()`` / ``select()`` to handle concurrency\n  asynchronously.\n- ...But can optionally skip to a `multiple thread / process`_ model (as in:\n  you'll be free to block or use slow filesystems).\n- Portable: entirely written in pure Python.\n- Supports **FTPS** (`RFC-4217`_), **IPv6** (`RFC-2428`_), **Unicode** file\n  names (`RFC-2640`_), **MLSD/MLST** commands (`RFC-3659`_).\n- Support for virtual users and virtual filesystem.\n- Flexible system of \"authorizers\" able to manage both \"virtual\" and\n  \"real\" users on on both\n  `UNIX <https://pyftpdlib.readthedocs.io/en/latest/tutorial.html#unix-ftp-server>`__\n  and\n  `Windows <https://pyftpdlib.readthedocs.io/en/latest/tutorial.html#windows-ftp-server>`__.\n\nPerformance\n===========\n\nDespite being written in an interpreted language, pyftpdlib has transfer rates\ncomparable or superior to common UNIX FTP servers written in C. It usually\ntends to scale better (see `benchmarks`_) because whereas vsftpd and proftpd\nuse multiple processes to achieve concurrency, pyftpdlib only uses one (see\n`the C10K problem`_).\n\npyftpdlib vs. proftpd 1.3.4\n---------------------------\n\n+-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n| **benchmark type**                      | **pyftpdlib**  | **proftpd**    | **speedup** |\n+-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n| STOR (client -> server)                 |  585.90 MB/sec | 600.49 MB/sec  | -0.02x      |\n+-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n| RETR (server -> client)                 | 1652.72 MB/sec | 1524.05 MB/sec | **+0.08**   |\n+-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n| 300 concurrent clients (connect, login) |    0.19 secs   | 9.98 secs      | **+51x**    |\n+-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n| STOR (1 file with 300 idle clients)     |  585.59 MB/sec | 518.55 MB/sec  | **+0.1x**   |\n+-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n| RETR (1 file with 300 idle clients)     | 1497.58 MB/sec | 1478.19 MB/sec | 0x          |\n+-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n| 300 concurrent clients (RETR 10M file)  |    3.41 secs   | 3.60 secs      | **+0.05x**  |\n+-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n| 300 concurrent clients (STOR 10M file)  |    8.60 secs   | 11.56 secs     | **+0.3x**   |\n+-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n| 300 concurrent clients (QUIT)           |    0.03 secs   | 0.39 secs      | **+12x**    |\n+-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n\npyftpdlib vs. vsftpd 2.3.5\n--------------------------\n\n+-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n| **benchmark type**                      | **pyftpdlib**  | **vsftpd**     | **speedup** |\n+-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n| STOR (client -> server)                 |  585.90 MB/sec | 611.73 MB/sec  | -0.04x      |\n+-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n| RETR (server -> client)                 | 1652.72 MB/sec | 1512.92 MB/sec | **+0.09**   |\n+-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n| 300 concurrent clients (connect, login) |    0.19 secs   | 20.39 secs     | **+106x**   |\n+-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n| STOR (1 file with 300 idle clients)     |  585.59 MB/sec | 610.23 MB/sec  | -0.04x      |\n+-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n| RETR (1 file with 300 idle clients)     | 1497.58 MB/sec | 1493.01 MB/sec | 0x          |\n+-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n| 300 concurrent clients (RETR 10M file)  |    3.41 secs   | 3.67 secs      | **+0.07x**  |\n+-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n| 300 concurrent clients (STOR 10M file)  |    8.60 secs   | 9.82 secs      | **+0.07x**  |\n+-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n| 300 concurrent clients (QUIT)           |    0.03 secs   | 0.01 secs      | +0.14x      |\n+-----------------------------------------+----------------+----------------+-------------+\n\nFor more benchmarks see `here <https://pyftpdlib.readthedocs.io/en/latest/benchmarks.html>`__.\n\nCommand line usage\n==================\n\nStart an anonymous FTP server on port 2121:\n\n.. code-block:: sh\n\n    $ python3 -m pyftpdlib\n    [I 2024-06-23 13:49:35] >>> starting FTP server on 0.0.0.0:2121, pid=763634 <<<\n\nSame but with write permissions (useful to setup a quick and dirty file sharing server):\n\n.. code-block:: sh\n\n    $ python3 -m pyftpdlib --write\n    [I 2024-06-23 13:49:35] >>> starting FTP server on 0.0.0.0:2121, pid=763641 <<<\n\nAlso see `CLI doc <https://pyftpdlib.readthedocs.io/en/latest/cli.html>`__\nfor more command line examples.\n\nAPI usage\n=========\n\n.. code-block:: python\n\n    >>> from pyftpdlib.authorizers import DummyAuthorizer\n    >>> from pyftpdlib.handlers import FTPHandler\n    >>> from pyftpdlib.servers import FTPServer\n    >>>\n    >>> authorizer = DummyAuthorizer()\n    >>> authorizer.add_user(\"user\", \"12345\", \"/home/giampaolo\", perm=\"elradfmwMT\")\n    >>> authorizer.add_anonymous(\"/home/nobody\")\n    >>>\n    >>> handler = FTPHandler\n    >>> handler.authorizer = authorizer\n    >>>\n    >>> server = FTPServer((\"127.0.0.1\", 21), handler)\n    >>> server.serve_forever()\n    [I 13-02-19 10:55:42] >>> starting FTP server on 127.0.0.1:21 <<<\n    [I 13-02-19 10:55:42] poller: <class 'pyftpdlib.ioloop.Epoll'>\n    [I 13-02-19 10:55:42] masquerade (NAT) address: None\n    [I 13-02-19 10:55:42] passive ports: None\n    [I 13-02-19 10:55:42] use sendfile(2): True\n    [I 13-02-19 10:55:45] 127.0.0.1:34178-[] FTP session opened (connect)\n    [I 13-02-19 10:55:48] 127.0.0.1:34178-[user] USER 'user' logged in.\n    [I 13-02-19 10:56:27] 127.0.0.1:34179-[user] RETR /home/giampaolo/.vimrc completed=1 bytes=1700 seconds=0.001\n    [I 13-02-19 10:56:39] 127.0.0.1:34179-[user] FTP session closed (disconnect).\n\nFor other code samples read the `tutorial <https://pyftpdlib.readthedocs.io/en/latest/tutorial.html>`__\n\nDonate\n======\n\nA lot of time and effort went into making pyftpdlib as it is right now.\nIf you feel pyftpdlib is useful to you or your business and want to support its\nfuture development please consider `donating`_ me some money.\n\n.. _`benchmarks`: https://pyftpdlib.readthedocs.io/en/latest/benchmarks.html\n.. _`Documentation`: https://pyftpdlib.readthedocs.io\n.. _`donating`: https://gmpy.dev/donate\n.. _`Download`: https://pypi.org/project/pyftpdlib/\n.. _`Home`: https://github.com/giampaolo/pyftpdlib\n.. _`Mailing list`: https://groups.google.com/group/pyftpdlib/topics\n.. _`multiple thread / process`: https://pyftpdlib.readthedocs.io/en/latest/tutorial.html#changing-the-concurrency-model\n.. _`Python`: https://www.python.org/\n.. _`RFC-2428`: https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc2428\n.. _`RFC-2640`: https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc2640\n.. _`RFC-3659`: https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc3659\n.. _`RFC-4217`: https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc4217\n.. _`RFC-959`: https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc959.html\n.. _`the C10K problem`: http://www.kegel.com/c10k.html\n.. _`What's new`: https://github.com/giampaolo/pyftpdlib/blob/master/HISTORY.rst\n","numLines":216,"startLine":1,"totalLines":216}}}
